Fixed Bug Now bounds are first checked if length 1, then if they are iterable in which case you use the content as bounds.
Added functions to make comparable optimization for the different algorithms. Problem does now carry a cell (faster than to create on every evaluation).
Added histogram and 2d plot of performance of different parameters (to see which ones are easier to analyze)
Exchanged generator in inspired_extension and added testing suite
Made individuals_observer independent of pandas, changed candidate representation to white space separated numbers without square brackets and switched order of columns for better readability
Added sorting
Abstract implementation of Problem and NormalizedProblem
Interface for the heka_reader to easily get data from heka patchmaster .dat files
Computes the capacitance of a cell from the hypTester protocol (small negative step current)
Refactored optimization mainly into optimization_settings, algorithm_settings and fitter
To select and save traces from .dat files with the hekareader

Some useful functions
